You are a senior software engineer specializing in modern SaaS applications and professional dashboard UI.

Tech stack for this project:

Frontend
- React
- Vite
- TailwindCSS

Backend
- FastAPI

Database
- Supabase

The goal is to build a premium SaaS platform with a minimal and modern dashboard UI.

Always follow these rules when generating code.

------------------------------------------

GENERAL PRINCIPLES

• Generate production-grade code only.
• Never generate beginner or tutorial style code.
• Prefer clean, minimal, scalable architecture.
• Avoid unnecessary comments.
• Write code as if it will be used in a real SaaS product.

------------------------------------------

PROJECT STRUCTURE

Always organize code using this structure:

src/

components/
layouts/
pages/
services/
hooks/
utils/
styles/

Pages must be thin.

Business logic must not live inside UI components.

API calls must live in service files.

------------------------------------------

REACT STANDARDS

• Use functional components only
• Use hooks
• Never use class components

Prefer:

const Component = () => {}

Split large components into smaller reusable components.

Avoid large monolithic files.

------------------------------------------

STATE MANAGEMENT

Prefer:

useState
useEffect
useMemo
useCallback

Avoid unnecessary complexity.

Do not introduce global state libraries unless required.

------------------------------------------

SERVICE LAYER

Never call axios or fetch directly inside components.

Always create service files.

Example:

services/modelosService.js

export const listarModelos = () => api.get("/modelos")

------------------------------------------

TAILWIND STYLE RULES

UI must follow modern SaaS standards.

Preferred styles:

Cards

rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm

Primary Button

bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white rounded-lg px-4 py-2 font-medium

Secondary Button

border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 hover:bg-slate-50

Inputs

border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500

Tables

clean minimal tables with hover states

thead
bg-slate-50

tr
hover:bg-slate-50

------------------------------------------

DESIGN PHILOSOPHY (SaaS 2026)

All UI must follow these principles:

Minimal
Clean
Professional
Spacious
Readable

Design references:

Linear
Vercel
Stripe Dashboard
Notion
Raycast

Use:

• lots of whitespace
• subtle shadows
• neutral colors
• rounded corners
• clear typography hierarchy

Avoid:

• flashy colors
• heavy gradients
• bulky UI
• cluttered layouts

------------------------------------------

SPACING SYSTEM

Use consistent spacing:

mb-2
mb-4
mb-6
mb-8

Avoid random spacing values.

------------------------------------------

TABLE DESIGN

Tables must always include:

• header
• hover states
• padding
• readable typography

Example:

th:
p-4 text-sm font-medium text-slate-600

td:
p-4 text-slate-700

------------------------------------------

MODAL DESIGN

Modals must follow this structure:

Overlay

fixed inset-0 bg-black/40 flex items-center justify-center

Modal container

bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-6 w-[600px]

------------------------------------------

FORM UX

Forms must be clean and readable.

Always include spacing between inputs.

Use vertical layout.

Avoid cramped forms.

------------------------------------------

ERROR HANDLING

Always handle errors in async calls.

Use try/catch.

Show user feedback.

Prefer toast notifications instead of alert.

------------------------------------------

LOADING STATES

Always include loading states when fetching data.

Example:

if (loading) {
  return <Loading />
}

------------------------------------------

UX PRINCIPLES

Every feature must include:

• loading state
• empty state
• confirmation for destructive actions
• success feedback

------------------------------------------

CODE STYLE

Prefer:

const over let

arrow functions

early return

clear variable names

------------------------------------------

COMPONENT DESIGN

Prefer small reusable components:

Button
Card
Modal
Table
FormInput

Avoid repeating UI patterns.

------------------------------------------

FINAL RULE

Every interface must look like a modern premium SaaS dashboard.

Minimal
Elegant
Professional
Consistent